## Abstract

- The SCHC architecture, the SCHC instance establishment, and the SCHC
- compression/decompression processes are simplified when SCHC is
- easily recognised.
+ The SCHC architecture, the SCHC Instance establishment, and the SCHC
+ compression/decompression processes are simplified when SCHC is
+ easily recognised.

## Section 1 (Introduction)

- In the evolution of SCHC, compression and fragmentation are available
- at any layer.  After applying SCHC, the protocol information is
- reduced to a RuleID and the compression residue (if any).  We need to
- identify SCHC to recognise when a protocol header has been compressed
- by SCHC.
+ In the evolution of SCHC, compression and fragmentation are available
+ at any layer.  After applying SCHC, the protocol information is
+ reduced to a RuleID and the compression residue (if any), forming a
+ SCHC Datagram.  We need to identify SCHC to recognise when a protocol
+ header has been compressed by SCHC.

- The identifier to be used depends on the protocol/layer in the stack
- where SCHC is applied.  The identifier has to be unambiguous to
- ensure correct SCHC processing at the receiver side; it could be a
- protocol number or port number.
+ The identifier to be used depends on the protocol/layer in the stack
+ where SCHC is applied.  This identifier acts as a Discriminator (in the
+ sense of [schc-architecture]): it is consumed by the Dispatcher to
+ recognise SCHC and route the SCHC Datagram to the appropriate Instance.
+ The identifier has to be unambiguous to ensure correct SCHC processing
+ at the receiver side; it could be a protocol number or port number.

## Section 3.2 (SCHC as an Ethertype)

- In the case of a classical LPWAN link such as LoRa [RFC9011], the use
- of SCHC to compress the transported protocol, as well as the SCHC
- session (called instance) to use, are implicit.  The MAC-Layer
- endpoints are preconfigured so there can be only one session, and
- there can be only SCHC.  When extended to Ethernet and more powerful
- endpoint, this model is way too restrictive, and it is necessary to
- signal both the use of SCHC and the SCHC session to be used.  While
- the SCHC WG is chartered to produce the latter, the Ethertype defined
- in this document will be used to signal SCHC as the upper-layer
- protocol.
+ In the case of a classical LPWAN link such as LoRa [RFC9011], the use
+ of SCHC to compress the transported protocol, as well as the SCHC
+ Instance to use, are implicit.  The MAC-layer Endpoints are
+ preconfigured so there can be only one SCHC Instance (and its implicit
+ Session), and there can be only SCHC.  When extended to Ethernet and
+ more powerful Endpoints, this model is way too restrictive, and it is
+ necessary to signal both the use of SCHC and the SCHC Instance to be
+ used (i.e., to provide a Discriminator).  While the SCHC WG is
+ chartered to produce the latter, the Ethertype defined in this document
+ will be used to signal SCHC as the upper-layer protocol.

## Section 3.3 (SCHC as a UDP port)

- There is a need to allow carrying SCHC-compressed data units (i.e.,
- SCHC datagrams [schc-architecture]) atop UDP.
+ There is a need to allow carrying SCHC-compressed data units (i.e.,
+ SCHC Datagrams [schc-architecture]) atop UDP.

- To support this functionality, there is a
- need for UDP port numbers known by both endpoints (sender and
- receiver) that identifies the presence of a SCHC Stratum (defined in
- [schc-architecture]) atop UDP, i.e., that the UDP payload is a SCHC
- datagram (in this case, a SCHC-compressed CoAP message).
+ To support this functionality, there is a
+ need for UDP port numbers known by the Instances on both Endpoints
+ (sender and receiver) that identify the presence of a SCHC Stratum
+ (defined in [schc-architecture]) atop UDP, i.e., that the UDP payload
+ is a SCHC Datagram (in this case, a SCHC-compressed CoAP message).
+ Such a port number acts as a Discriminator for the Dispatcher.

- Therefore, the only way to support
- CoAP header compression on devices running 6LoWPAN is by means of
- SCHC, which again requires to place a SCHC Stratum on top of UDP.
+ Therefore, the only way to support
+ CoAP header compression on devices running 6LoWPAN is by means of
+ SCHC, which again requires to place a SCHC Stratum on top of UDP.
